* Learning and applying data analytics techniques while utilizing problem solving skills to conduct quantitative and qualitative analyses using a diverse set of technology applications and tools (i.e. Excel, SQL, R, Python, Tableau, Alteryx, etc).
* Utilizing critical thinking that breaks down complex problems, understands root causes, and proposes viable solutions while maintaining quality;
* Working in collaborative and team based environment, delivering with diverse global client, PwC and third-party teams;
* Demonstrating ability to learn accounting principles and business processes;
* Demonstrating ability to learn how to evaluate, cleanse, design, and implement data models using data mining techniques;
* Understanding business intelligence and relational database concepts, as well as big data objectives, concepts, and technologies such as Hadoop;
* Demonstrating ability to identify and incorporate tools and techniques using technology applications (e.g. Microsoft SQL Server, ACL, Access/Excel, Visual Basic, R, Python, SAS, Stata, Alteryx) and build reporting capabilities through data visualization (e.g. Tableau, Spotfire, Qlikview, Einstein Analytics);
* Demonstrating knowledge of descriptive analytics, predictive analytics, machine learning principles, AI, robotic process automation (RPA), project management, software and solution implementation methodologies;
* Demonstrating interest to independently learn business processes and technologies, in particular, ERP, GRC and CRM solutions; and,
* Understanding various facets of business and/or IT processes, concepts of enterprise risk, internal controls, ERPs and CRMs, cloud solutions, corporate compliance and regulatory mandates, portfolio, program, and agile team management, technical aspects of information systems, financial reporting concepts, and systems development methodology.


